.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::ClassifiedListing \- NIP\-99 classified listings
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::ClassifiedListing;
\&
\&    my $pubkey = \*(Aqaa\*(Aq x 32;
\&
\&    # Create a classified listing (kind 30402)
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::ClassifiedListing\->listing(
\&        pubkey       => $pubkey,
\&        content      => "# Vintage Guitar\en\enGreat condition, barely played.",
\&        identifier   => \*(Aqvintage\-guitar\*(Aq,
\&        title        => \*(AqVintage Guitar\*(Aq,
\&        summary      => \*(AqA beautiful vintage guitar in great condition\*(Aq,
\&        published_at => 1296962229,
\&        location     => \*(AqNYC\*(Aq,
\&        price        => [\*(Aq500\*(Aq, \*(AqUSD\*(Aq],
\&        status       => \*(Aqactive\*(Aq,
\&        hashtags     => [\*(Aqmusic\*(Aq, \*(Aqinstruments\*(Aq],
\&        images       => [
\&            [\*(Aqhttps://example.com/guitar1.jpg\*(Aq, \*(Aq800x600\*(Aq],
\&            [\*(Aqhttps://example.com/guitar2.jpg\*(Aq],
\&        ],
\&    );
\&
\&    # Create a draft/inactive listing (kind 30403, same structure)
\&    my $draft = Net::Nostr::ClassifiedListing\->draft(
\&        pubkey     => $pubkey,
\&        content    => "# WIP Listing\en\enNot ready yet.",
\&        identifier => \*(Aqmy\-draft\*(Aq,
\&        title      => \*(AqWork in Progress\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Recurring price (e.g. monthly rent)
\&    my $rental = Net::Nostr::ClassifiedListing\->listing(
\&        pubkey     => $pubkey,
\&        content    => "Apartment for rent.",
\&        identifier => \*(Aqapartment\-rent\*(Aq,
\&        title      => \*(Aq2BR Apartment\*(Aq,
\&        price      => [\*(Aq1500\*(Aq, \*(AqUSD\*(Aq, \*(Aqmonth\*(Aq],
\&        location   => \*(AqBrooklyn\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Parse listing metadata from an event
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::ClassifiedListing\->from_event($event);
\&    say $info\->title;        # \*(AqVintage Guitar\*(Aq
\&    say $info\->location;     # \*(AqNYC\*(Aq
\&    say $info\->price\->[0];   # \*(Aq500\*(Aq
\&    say $info\->price\->[1];   # \*(AqUSD\*(Aq
\&
\&    # Generate an naddr for linking
\&    my $naddr = Net::Nostr::ClassifiedListing\->to_naddr($event,
\&        relays => [\*(Aqwss://relay.example.com\*(Aq],
\&    );
\&
\&    # Validate a listing event
\&    Net::Nostr::ClassifiedListing\->validate($event);
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-99 classified listings. Classified listings are kind 30402
addressable events that describe products, services, or other things for
sale or offer. The structure is similar to NIP\-23 long\-form content, with
additional metadata tags for pricing, location, and status.
.PP
Content should be a Markdown description of what is being offered. The
\&\f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR field identifies the party creating the listing.
.PP
Draft or inactive listings use kind 30403, which has the same structure
as kind 30402.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 1
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::ClassifiedListing\->new(%fields);
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::ClassifiedListing\*(C'\fR object. Typically returned by
"from_event"; calling \f(CW\*(C`new\*(C'\fR directly is useful for testing or
manual construction.
.PP
.Vb 6
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::ClassifiedListing\->new(
\&        identifier => \*(Aqmy\-listing\*(Aq,
\&        title      => \*(AqGuitar\*(Aq,
\&        price      => \*(Aq500 USD\*(Aq,
\&        location   => \*(AqNYC\*(Aq,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Accepted fields: \f(CW\*(C`identifier\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`title\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`summary\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`published_at\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`location\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`price\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`status\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`images\*(C'\fR (defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR),
\&\f(CW\*(C`hashtags\*(C'\fR (defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR). Croaks on unknown arguments.
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS listing
.IX Subsection "listing"
.Vb 10
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::ClassifiedListing\->listing(
\&        pubkey       => $hex_pubkey,         # required
\&        content      => $markdown,           # required
\&        identifier   => \*(Aqlisting\-slug\*(Aq,      # required (d tag)
\&        title        => \*(AqListing Title\*(Aq,     # optional
\&        summary      => \*(AqShort tagline.\*(Aq,    # optional
\&        published_at => 1296962229,          # optional (unix timestamp)
\&        location     => \*(AqNYC\*(Aq,               # optional
\&        price        => [\*(Aq100\*(Aq, \*(AqUSD\*(Aq],      # optional
\&        status       => \*(Aqactive\*(Aq,            # optional ("active" or "sold")
\&        hashtags     => [\*(Aqelectronics\*(Aq],      # optional (t tags)
\&        images       => [[\*(Aqurl\*(Aq, \*(Aq256x256\*(Aq]],# optional (image tags)
\&        extra_tags   => [[\*(Aqg\*(Aq, \*(Aqdr5regw\*(Aq]],  # optional (additional tags)
\&        created_at   => time(),              # optional
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 30402 classified listing Net::Nostr::Event. \f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`content\*(C'\fR, and \f(CW\*(C`identifier\*(C'\fR are required.
.PP
The \f(CW\*(C`price\*(C'\fR parameter is an arrayref of \f(CW\*(C`[amount, currency]\*(C'\fR or
\&\f(CW\*(C`[amount, currency, frequency]\*(C'\fR where currency is an ISO 4217 code
(or crypto code like \f(CW\*(C`btc\*(C'\fR) and frequency is optional (e.g. \f(CW\*(C`month\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`year\*(C'\fR).
.PP
.Vb 2
\&    # One\-time: $50 USD
\&    price => [\*(Aq50\*(Aq, \*(AqUSD\*(Aq]
\&
\&    # Recurring: 15 EUR/month
\&    price => [\*(Aq15\*(Aq, \*(AqEUR\*(Aq, \*(Aqmonth\*(Aq]
.Ve
.PP
The \f(CW\*(C`images\*(C'\fR parameter is an arrayref of arrayrefs. Each inner arrayref
contains a URL and an optional dimensions string (\f(CW\*(C`WxH\*(C'\fR in pixels), per
NIP\-58.
.PP
.Vb 4
\&    images => [
\&        [\*(Aqhttps://example.com/photo.jpg\*(Aq, \*(Aq800x600\*(Aq],
\&        [\*(Aqhttps://example.com/detail.jpg\*(Aq],
\&    ]
.Ve
.SS draft
.IX Subsection "draft"
.Vb 6
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::ClassifiedListing\->draft(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,
\&        content    => $markdown,
\&        identifier => \*(Aqdraft\-slug\*(Aq,
\&        # same optional params as listing()
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 30403 draft/inactive listing. Accepts the same parameters
as "listing".
.SS from_event
.IX Subsection "from_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::ClassifiedListing\->from_event($event);
.Ve
.PP
Parses listing metadata from a kind 30402 or 30403 Net::Nostr::Event.
Returns a \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::ClassifiedListing\*(C'\fR object with accessors, or
\&\f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if the event is not a listing kind.
.PP
.Vb 4
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::ClassifiedListing\->from_event($event);
\&    say $info\->identifier;   # \*(Aqmy\-listing\*(Aq
\&    say $info\->title;        # \*(AqVintage Guitar\*(Aq or undef
\&    say $info\->price\->[1] if $info\->price;  # \*(AqUSD\*(Aq
.Ve
.SS validate
.IX Subsection "validate"
.Vb 1
\&    Net::Nostr::ClassifiedListing\->validate($event);
.Ve
.PP
Validates that an event is a well\-formed NIP\-99 listing. Croaks if:
.IP \(bu 4
Kind is not 30402 or 30403
.IP \(bu 4
Missing \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag
.PP
.Vb 2
\&    eval { Net::Nostr::ClassifiedListing\->validate($event) };
\&    warn "Invalid listing: $@" if $@;
.Ve
.SS to_naddr
.IX Subsection "to_naddr"
.Vb 3
\&    my $naddr = Net::Nostr::ClassifiedListing\->to_naddr($event,
\&        relays => [\*(Aqwss://relay.com\*(Aq],
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Generates a NIP\-19 \f(CW\*(C`naddr\*(C'\fR bech32 string for linking to the listing.
The \f(CW\*(C`relays\*(C'\fR parameter is optional.
.SH ACCESSORS
.IX Header "ACCESSORS"
These are available on objects returned by "from_event".
.SS identifier
.IX Subsection "identifier"
.Vb 1
\&    my $id = $info\->identifier;
.Ve
.PP
The \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag value identifying the listing.
.SS title
.IX Subsection "title"
.Vb 1
\&    my $title = $info\->title;  # or undef
.Ve
.PP
The listing title, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if not set.
.SS summary
.IX Subsection "summary"
.Vb 1
\&    my $text = $info\->summary;  # or undef
.Ve
.PP
Short tagline or summary for the listing, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR.
.SS published_at
.IX Subsection "published_at"
.Vb 1
\&    my $ts = $info\->published_at;  # \*(Aq1296962229\*(Aq or undef
.Ve
.PP
The original publication timestamp (stringified unix seconds), or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR.
.SS location
.IX Subsection "location"
.Vb 1
\&    my $loc = $info\->location;  # \*(AqNYC\*(Aq or undef
.Ve
.PP
The listing location, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR.
.SS price
.IX Subsection "price"
.Vb 1
\&    my $price = $info\->price;  # [\*(Aq100\*(Aq, \*(AqUSD\*(Aq] or [\*(Aq15\*(Aq, \*(AqEUR\*(Aq, \*(Aqmonth\*(Aq] or undef
.Ve
.PP
Arrayref of \f(CW\*(C`[amount, currency]\*(C'\fR or \f(CW\*(C`[amount, currency, frequency]\*(C'\fR,
or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if no price tag is present.
.SS status
.IX Subsection "status"
.Vb 1
\&    my $status = $info\->status;  # \*(Aqactive\*(Aq, \*(Aqsold\*(Aq, or undef
.Ve
.PP
The listing status, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR.
.SS images
.IX Subsection "images"
.Vb 1
\&    my $imgs = $info\->images;  # [[\*(Aqurl\*(Aq, \*(Aq256x256\*(Aq], [\*(Aqurl2\*(Aq]]
.Ve
.PP
Arrayref of arrayrefs, each containing a URL and optional dimensions.
Empty arrayref if no image tags are present.
.SS hashtags
.IX Subsection "hashtags"
.Vb 1
\&    my $tags = $info\->hashtags;  # [\*(Aqelectronics\*(Aq, \*(Aqgadgets\*(Aq]
.Ve
.PP
Arrayref of hashtag strings from \f(CW\*(C`t\*(C'\fR tags. Empty arrayref if none.
